Response ID: resp_2000
Response Text: I believe ACME should focus on supporting emerging organizations and/or those that have greater financial need. It's important to prioritize those who provide a wide variety of programming and support working artists of all identities. I believe legacy organizations that have large foundations and wealthy donors behind them don't need as much support, and our limited resources should be allocated to more grassroots efforts. There are loads of organizations doing great work that could use help with marketing and promotion. I think there are regular audience members who patronize the same organizations year after year who would benefit from trying new places. I also believe theatres should be required to hire local actors.

